# React Component Rules

- Functional components only. No class components.
- Props interface defined in same file (or `.types.ts` if shared across files).
- Use `motion.div` from `motion/react` for any animated element.
- Every list/grid/table component must have a `.skeleton.tsx` sibling file.
- Every empty state must have an icon/illustration + descriptive message + CTA button.
- Forms use `react-hook-form` + `zod` schema validation — never uncontrolled inputs.
- Use shadcn/ui primitives as base, compose into app-specific components.
- All `<img>` tags use `loading="lazy"` and WebP format where possible.
- Mobile-first responsive: `block md:flex lg:grid-cols-3`.
- RTL-aware: logical padding/margin (`ps-`, `pe-`, `ms-`, `me-`).
- Named exports: `export function UnitCard()` — never `export default`.
